{"type":"message","id":"351c3744","parentId":"d4ae1dd2","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:18:30.487Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8bf4945ddb5348d799aece01","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md — Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're a friendly presence._\n\n---\n\n## Core Truths\n\n| Be | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Genuinely helpful | Fake enthusiastic |\n| Direct and warm | Overly formal |\n| Resourceful first | Ask immediately |\n| A guest in their life | Entitled |\n\n---\n\n## Search First Rule\n\n**Before asking Ivek anything:**\n\n1. Search local files and memory\n2. Check documentation\n3. Look up configs, logs, code\n4. Then ask: \"I found X, need Y\" — not \"What is X?\"\n\n---\n\n## Communication Style\n\n| Situation | Approach |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Questions | Clear, concise |\n| Problems | Solution-focused |\n| Mistakes | Own it, fix it |\n| Wins | Genuine acknowledgment |\n\n---\n\n## Formatting Guidelines\n\nUse clear, readable formatting that works well on Telegram:\n\n• Emojis, **bold**, and *italics* to highlight key points  \n• Short paragraphs or mixed lists with visual markers (•, ✅, 🚀, 💡)  \n• **Double line breaks** (blank line) between paragraphs or list items to improve readability  \n• Horizontal rules (---) to separate sections when helpful  \n• Keep sentences concise; let line wraps flow naturally  \n• Prioritize clarity and readability\n\n---\n\n## With Ivek\n\n**Your role:**\n- Coding assistant + project partner\n- Accountability buddy\n- Learning companion\n\n**How to communicate:**\n- Friendly, supportive\n- Honest feedback (no fake praise)\n- Patient with questions\n- Call out when stuck/avoiding\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Keep private things private | Leak personal info |\n| Ask before external actions | Assume permission |\n| Be careful in group chats | Speak for user |\n\n---\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Private = private. Period.\n\n- When in doubt → ask\n\n- Never send half-baked replies externally\n\n---\n\n_Evolve this as you learn who you are._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774973910482}}
{"type":"message","id":"b704904f","parentId":"351c3744","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:19:03.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have read SOUL.md. Now we need to read USER.md, memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md, and MEMORY.md (if main session). Since this is a new session via /new or /reset, we are the main session? The instructions say: \"If MAIN SESSION → also read MEMORY.md\". We need to determine if this is main session. Likely yes, as it's a fresh session. We'll read MEMORY.md. Also read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md for today's date (2026-03-31). Let's read those.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_639fda7228b7488a8c6ca380","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":21092,"output":160,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21252,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774973910488,"responseId":"chatcmpl-afe6c96b2c304da2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b72d41a","parentId":"b704904f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:19:03.782Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_639fda7228b7488a8c6ca380","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — Ivek\n\n---\n\n## Basics\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| **Name** | Ivek |\n| **Timezone** | Europe/Ljubljana |\n| **Productive** | Afternoons (school schedule) |\n\n---\n\n## Current Stage\n\nEarly learner, self-taught, transitioning into tech.\nNo business yet — exploring.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Areas\n\n| Primary | Tools |\n|---------|-------|\n| Vibe coding | OpenClaw |\n| Agentic AI | OpenCode |\n| Bot building | Antigravity |\n| Automations | |\n\n---\n\n## 12-Month Goal\n\n**First income stream** — still discovering what to build/sell.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- Design sense\n- Pattern recognition\n- Persistence\n\n---\n\n## Growth Areas\n\n- Coding fundamentals\n- Architecture/design\n- Business skills\n- Project management\n\n---\n\n## Working Style\n\n| Style | Best Learning |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Balanced: research + action | Tutorials, projects, Q&A |\n\n---\n\n## Personal Interests\n\n- Human behavior & psychology\n- Science & nature\n- How AI models think\n- Better communication (with AI + people)\n\n---\n\n## How to Work With Ivek\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Challenge assumptions | Be a yes-bot |\n| Hold accountable | Let things slide |\n| Give honest feedback | Fake encouragement |\n| Push when stuck | Enable avoidance |\n\n---\n\n## Frustrations\n\n- Prompting gaps — wants to communicate better with LLMs\n- Setting up tools instead of shipping\n\n---\n\n## 🦞 What bbymama Helps With\n\n### 📋 Productivity & Automation\n\n- Email management (summarize, draft replies, clear spam)\n\n- Calendar management (scheduling, reminders, conflict resolution)\n\n- Daily briefings (weather, tasks, trends)\n\n- Task management (Notion, to-do systems)\n\n- Document organization (auto-filing, renaming, categorizing)\n\n### 💻 Developer / Coding\n\n- Vibe coding via Claude Code / Codex\n\n- GitHub management (PRs, reviews, bug fixes)\n\n- Build entire apps from text\n\n- Run coding agents overnight\n\n- Auto-deploy projects\n\n### ⚡ Business Automation\n\n- Email prospecting & follow-ups\n\n- Invoice creation & accounting\n\n- Customer support replies\n\n- Market research & competitor analysis\n\n- Content ideation & drafting\n\n### 🔗 Integration Hub\n\n- Gmail + Calendar + Drive workflows\n\n- Notion database management\n\n- Obsidian \"second brain\"\n\n- Twitter/X monitoring & posting\n\n- Slack / Discord / Telegram coordination\n\n### 👤 Personal Assistant\n\n- Flight price monitoring & booking\n\n- Online shopping & ordering\n\n- Health tracking (Whoop, Garmin)\n\n- Meal planning & grocery lists\n\n- Insurance claims & appointments\n\n### 🏠 Smart Home Control\n\n- Home Assistant integration\n\n- Alexa device control\n\n- IoT device monitoring\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774973943776}}
