{"type":"message","id":"aa0160d6","parentId":"dbdd5acb","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:22:25.300Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the OpenClaw configuration to add the researcher agent as per the user's request. Let me follow the steps they outlined:\n\nStep 1: Define the agent in agents.list[] - add researcher\nStep 2: Let agents.defaults handle baseline (already there)\nStep 3: Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents for orchestrator\nStep 4: Set cheaper model for subagents (researcher gets claude-sonnet-4)\nStep 5: Cap concurrency \nStep 6: Scope tool access\n\nBut wait, I need to check if there's an orchestrator agent already. Looking at the current config, I only see \"main\" agent. The user wants to add a researcher agent and configure the orchestrator to allow it.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the user's request, they want to:\n1. Add researcher agent to agents.list\n2. Configure orchestrator to allowAgents [\"researcher\", \"coder\"] \n3. Set model for researcher to anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\n4. Set maxConcurrency defaults\n5. Scope tool access for subagents\n\nBut I don't see an orchestrator agent in the current config. Let me check if I need to add that too, or if the user expects me to modify the existing main agent to be the orchestrator?\n\nLooking at the guidelines again, it seems like they want to set up a researcher agent that can be spawned by an orchestrator. Since I only see a \"main\" agent currently, I'll need to either:\n- Add both researcher and orchestrator agents\n- Or modify the main agent to be the orchestrator and add researcher\n\nLet me check if there are any existing orchestrator references... Actually, let me first just add the researcher agent as requested, and then we can see about the orchestrator.\n\nThe user said: \"Define the agent in agents.list[] — minimal config only\" and showed:\n{\n \"agents\": {\n \"list\": [{ \"id\": \"researcher\" }]\n }}\n\nSo I need to add a researcher object to the agents.list array.\n\nLet me also check if I need to add the orchestrator. The user mentioned orchestrator in step 3, so I probably need to add that too or modify main to be orchestrator.\n\nActually, looking at the current config, the main agent has identity info. It might be better to keep main as the user's primary agent and add orchestrator as a separate agent that can spawn subagents. But for simplicity, maybe I should just add researcher and configure the main agent's subagents settings.\n\nLet me proceed by:\n1. Adding researcher agent to agents.list\n2. Adding subagents configuration to the main agent (or adding orchestrator)\n3. Setting the model for researcher\n4. Setting maxConcurrency in agents.defaults\n5. Scoping tool access for subagents\n\nLet me make these changes to the openclaw.json file.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f043616478f64a47854d305a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw doctor"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":24748,"output":658,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25406,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774974124785,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a21c00009a580852"}}
