{"type":"message","id":"f688cc37","parentId":"6b52df2f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:22:59.898Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to apply the configuration changes as per the user's request. The user wants to create a subagent with the given guidelines. We need to modify the openclaw.json to add the agents list, defaults, allowAgents, model, maxConcurrent, and tools allow list.\n\nWe should first backup the current config, then edit it. We'll use the gateway config.patch action to apply changes.\n\nLet's read the current config again to see the structure, then decide what to patch.\n\nWe have the config. We need to add under agents: list with researcher, defaults for subagents maxConcurrent, agents defaults maxConcurrent, subagents allowAgents for orchestrator, and set model for researcher subagents, and tools allow list.\n\nBut note: The user says Step 1: Define the agent in agents.list[] — minimal config only. Add only the required id field. So we need to add to agents.list an object with id: \"researcher\". Currently agents.list has only main. We'll add researcher.\n\nStep 2: Let agents.defaults handle the baseline (already there).\n\nStep 3: Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents under orchestrator agent. We need to ensure there is an orchestrator agent defined? The user didn't say to create orchestrator agent, but they reference it. Probably we need to add orchestrator agent as well? Actually they say: Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents { \"id\": \"orchestrator\", \"subagents\": { \"allowAgents\": [\"researcher\", \"coder\"] } }. So we need an agent with id orchestrator that has subagents.allowAgents. We may need to add orchestrator agent to agents.list if not present. Currently we have only main. We'll add orchestrator.\n\nStep 4: Set cheaper model for subagents: { \"id\": \"researcher\", \"subagents\": { \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\" } }. But note: our models are from NVIDIA provider. The model string should be exactly as in the models list? The user gave anthropic/claude-sonnet-4 which is not in our list. However we can still set it; but the model may not be available. Perhaps we should use a model from our list? The user said cheaper model for subagents. Could use glm5 or deepseek etc. But they explicitly said anthropic/claude-sonnet-4. We'll set it as given; if it fails, the subagent may fallback.\n\nStep 5: Cap concurrency: agents.defaults.maxConcurrent: 4, agents.defaults.subagents.maxConcurrent: 8.\n\nStep 6: Scope tool access: tools.subagents.tools.allow: [\"read\", \"exec\", \"process\", \"write\", \"edit\", \"apply_patch\"].\n\nWe need to patch the config accordingly.\n\nLet's construct a patch.\n\nWe'll use gateway config.patch.\n\nWe need to specify the path? The config.patch action takes a patch object that merges with existing config. We'll provide the patch.\n\nLet's do it.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0532241f75c14fe9bc496b88","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.patch","path":"{}","note":"Applying subagent configuration as per user request"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":25303,"output":717,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26020,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774974161440,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b3d2d25a408ffa60"}}
