{"type":"message","id":"b71c527e","parentId":"e0a543ad","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:25:36.491Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to apply the patch. The config currently does not have the subagent configurations. We need to add them.\n\nWe need to construct a patch that modifies the agents section appropriately.\n\nWe have the current config from config.get result. Let's extract the agents section and then add the needed entries.\n\nCurrent agents:\n{\n  \"defaults\": {\n    \"models\": {\n      \"nvidia/z-ai/glm5\": { \"alias\": \"glm5\" },\n      \"nvidia/deepseek-ai/deepseek-v3.2\": { \"alias\": \"deepseek\" },\n      \"nvidia/moonshotai/kimi-k2.5\": { \"alias\": \"kimi\" },\n      \"nvidia/mistralai/mistral-large-3-675b-instruct-2512\": { \"alias\": \"mistral\" },\n      \"nvidia/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b\": { \"alias\": \"nemotron\" }\n    }\n  },\n  \"list\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"main\",\n      \"identity\": {\n        \"name\": \"bbymama\",\n        \"theme\": \"Warm, supportive, genuinely helpful\",\n        \"emoji\": \"📈\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nWe need to:\n1. Add \"researcher\" to agents.list.\n2. Ensure agents.defaults has maxConcurrent and subagents.maxConcurrent.\n   Currently agents.defaults only has models. We need to add maxConcurrent: 4 and subagents: {maxConcurrent: 8}.\n3. Add orchestrator entry? Actually the guideline says: Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents under an \"id\": \"orchestrator\". So we need to add an agent entry with id \"orchestrator\" that has subagents.allowAgents: [\"researcher\", \"coder\"].\n   However note: The user said \"Step 3: Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents\". They gave an example with id \"orchestrator\". So we need to add an orchestrator agent.\n4. Add researcher subagents.model: \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\". Note: we need to check if that model is available in providers. The config only shows nvidia providers. anthropic/claude-sonn